race.comment: STORM AWAY (1) is chasing a hat-trick after stepping up in class from a tough Belmont win to score over 1000m here nearly 4 weeks ago. He has plenty of scope, and there's no reason he can't get the job done again. MONTE TREMEZZO (5) finished off strongly when resuming to grab second behind the top pick over this trip at this track. He strips fitter, and can turn the tables. LIKE CLOCKWORK (8) made it 2 from 2 this campaign with a last-to-first win here just over 3 weeks ago. This is much tougher, but she is definitely worth considering for all combos. BABY PEARL (2) was below her best last time, finishing fifth and 3 lengths off over 1200m here 12 days ago. She seems more suited to the 1000m, and can bounce straight back into the money here. RIPPER RUPERT (3) was a comfortable winner fresh up, and though this is tougher, he is capable of figuring in the top four again.
